 "body": "<p>Rights to receive ground rents, perpetual chief rents etc, created by a trader should be dealt with, in the computation of profits and losses, in accordance with <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim51535\">BIM51535</a> onwards following the cases of CIR v John Emery &amp; Sons [1936] 20TC213, and B G Utting &amp; Co Ltd v Hughes [1940] 23TC174.</p>\n\n<p>The guidance on ground rents is arranged as follows.</p>\n",
